---

<PolicyPageLayout
  title="Terms of use"
  description="The practical rules for using evidique and relying on its independent software coverage."
  kicker="Reasonable rules, plain language"
  recordLabel="Site terms"
  {updatedAt}
  {sections}
  highlights={[
    'Reviews are general information, not legal, financial, or security advice.',
    'Verify prices, limits, and purchase terms with the software vendor.',
    'Linking and short attributed quotations are welcome; copying the site is not.',
  ]}
>
  <h2 id="accepting-these-terms">Accepting these terms</h2>
  <p>
    By accessing or using evidique, you agree to these terms and the linked
    <a href="/privacy-policy/">privacy policy</a>. If you do not agree, do not use the site.
  </p>
  <p>
    These terms apply only to evidique. A software vendor, affiliate network, or other linked site
    will have its own terms for your use or purchase.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-may-use-the-site">Who may use the site</h2>
  <p>
    You may use the site if you can legally agree to these terms where you live. If you use evidique
    for an organization, you confirm that you have authority to act for it.
  </p>

  <h2 id="editorial-information-not-advice">Editorial information, not advice</h2>
  <p>
    Reviews, comparisons, guides, scores, and comments are general editorial information. They are
    not legal, financial, tax, security, medical, or procurement advice, and they do not replace
    testing a product against your own requirements.
  </p>
  <p>
    A recommendation describes a product for the audience and use case stated on the page. It is not
    a promise that the same tool will suit every workflow, budget, data policy, or risk level.
  </p>

  <h2 id="accuracy-pricing-and-product-changes">Accuracy, pricing, and product changes</h2>
  <p>
    We work to support important claims with tests and dated sources, but software changes quickly.
    Features may move between plans, prices may vary by country or tax status, and a vendor may
    change or discontinue a product after our latest check.
  </p>
  <p>
    Verify critical details with the vendor before buying, migrating data, or deploying software.
    Publication and update dates tell you when our information was last reviewed; they do not make
    it real-time data.
  </p>

  <h2 id="third-party-products-and-purchases">Third-party products and purchases</h2>
  <p>
    evidique does not sell the software covered in its articles and is not a party to your purchase
    from a vendor. Billing, renewals, refunds, warranties, support, data handling, and service
    availability are governed by your agreement with that third party.
  </p>
  <p>
    A link does not guarantee that the destination is always safe, available, or unchanged. Use your
    own judgment before downloading software, granting permissions, or entering payment details.
  </p>

  <h2 id="affiliate-links">Affiliate links</h2>
  <p>
    Some clearly labeled links may generate a commission if you complete a qualifying purchase.
    Affiliate availability does not determine coverage, ranking, or verdicts. Read the full
    <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a> for how commercial links are handled.
  </p>

  <h2 id="intellectual-property">Intellectual property</h2>
  <p>
    Original text, graphics, page design, test records, and screenshots are protected by applicable
    intellectual-property law. Product names, logos, and third-party materials remain the property
    of their respective owners.
  </p>
  <p>
    You may link to evidique and quote short passages for commentary, reporting, or research when
    you preserve the meaning and provide clear attribution. You may not republish substantial
    portions, remove attribution, sell copies, or use automated extraction to reproduce the
    publication.
  </p>

  <h2 id="acceptable-use">Acceptable use</h2>
  <p>You must not use the site to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>break applicable law or infringe another person's rights;</li>
    <li>bypass access controls, probe security, or interfere with site operation;</li>
    <li>send malware, abusive traffic, or automated requests that degrade the service;</li>
    <li>misrepresent evidique content, scores, endorsements, or affiliation.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Ordinary browsing, search-engine crawling that respects published directives, citation, and
    accessibility tools are welcome.
  </p>

  <h2 id="availability-and-changes">Availability and changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may correct, update, reorganize, suspend, or remove content without promising permanent
    coverage of a product. We do not guarantee uninterrupted access or that every old link will keep
    working forever.
  </p>

  <h2 id="disclaimers">Disclaimers</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, evidique is provided “as is” and “as available,” without
    warranties of accuracy, completeness, merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or
    non-infringement. Nothing in these terms excludes a warranty that cannot legally be excluded.
  </p>

  <h2 id="limitation-of-liability">Limitation of liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the maximum extent permitted by law, evidique and its operator will not be liable for
    indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive loss arising from your use of the site
    or reliance on its content. This includes lost profits, lost data, business interruption, and
    costs caused by a third-party product or service.
  </p>
  <p>
    These limits do not apply where the law does not allow them. Your mandatory consumer rights
    remain unaffected.
  </p>

  <h2 id="general-terms">General terms</h2>
  <p>
    If part of these terms is found unenforceable, the remaining terms continue to apply. A delay in
    enforcing a term does not waive it. These terms and the policies linked from them form the
    entire agreement about your use of evidique.
  </p>
  <p>
    We may update these terms when the site or legal requirements change. The effective date at the
    top will change with a material revision. Continued use after an update means the revised terms
    apply from that date, subject to any notice required by law.
  </p>

  <h2 id="contact">Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about these terms can be sent to
    <a href="mailto:x771364026@gmail.com">x771364026@gmail.com</a>.
  </p>
</PolicyPageLayout>
